## RTK CLI (v0.34.3)

High-performance CLI proxy — filters/summarizes system output before reaching LLM context.
Path: `~/.cargo/bin/rtk`. Use in built-in terminal for any shell command.

### Key Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `rtk ls` | Token-optimized directory listing |
| `rtk tree` | Directory tree with token optimization |
| `rtk read <file>` | Read file with intelligent filtering |
| `rtk diff` | Ultra-condensed diff (only changed lines) |
| `rtk grep <pattern>` | Compact grep, groups by file |
| `rtk test` | Run tests, show only failures |
| `rtk err <cmd>` | Run command, show only errors/warnings |
| `rtk log` | Filter/deduplicate log output |
| `rtk git`, `rtk gh`, `rtk glab` | Git/GitHub/GitLab with compact output |
| `rtk docker`, `rtk kubectl` | Docker/K8s with compact output |
| `rtk pnpm`, `rtk dotnet` | Package manager compact output |
| `rtk env` | Environment vars (sensitive masked) |
| `rtk deps` | Summarize project dependencies |
| `rtk summary <cmd>` | Heuristic summary of any command |

**When to use:** Always prepend `rtk` to terminal commands when output would be verbose. Saves tokens, keeps context clean.
